Homaro Cantu was found hanging inside Crooked Fork Brewery in Chicago on Tuesday  . 
  The married father of two was the owner of Michelin-starred restaurant Moto  . 
  He was hit with a lawsuit last month from a former investor in Moto and failed restaurant iNG  . 
  Authorities are investigating his death as a suicide . 
  Cantu worked for Charlie Trotter from 1999 until 2003 . 
  He was known as a pioneer in the field of molecular gastronomy . 
 